1694
02:37:16,843 --> 02:37:19,267
And I've heard from folks on both sides of that.

1695
02:37:20,371 --> 02:37:22,752
who are very frustrated with this.

1696
02:37:22,892 --> 02:37:27,593
And some of those folks are saying, I would never support this, period, no matter what the rollout was.

1697
02:37:28,033 --> 02:37:41,098
And some folks are saying, this actually, I support it 100%, but I'm worried about, and it would work for my house, but I'm worried about the people who it won't work for, and I don't know what the plan is, and I'm worried about what the negative impacts are going to be.

1698
02:37:41,978 --> 02:37:46,799
So that's why I co-sponsored this resolution with Councilor Callahan.

1699
02:37:46,899 --> 02:37:48,500
I think really,

1700
02:37:50,682 --> 02:37:52,343
put the cart before the horse on this one.

1701
02:37:53,244 --> 02:37:56,167
And I'm very concerned about this change.

1702
02:37:58,088 --> 02:37:58,909
What are councilors saying?

1703
02:38:02,632 --> 02:38:07,816
Thank you, President Behrs and Councilor Callahan for introducing this resolution.

1704
02:38:08,797 --> 02:38:16,183
Reducing waste, saving taxpayer money and preparing residents for potential statewide food waste ban are all important noble goals, but

1705
02:38:16,700 --> 02:38:28,342
burying what feels like an austerity cut to waste services inside an opaque press release about grant funding has caused real frustration and undermined trust with residents, and frankly, with counselors as well.

1706
02:38:29,142 --> 02:38:35,323
Many of us, including those of us on this council, learned about the administration's final decision through social media.

1707
02:38:36,104 --> 02:38:44,125
This is exactly the kind of governance by press release I've spoke strongly against years ago, and I'm going to speak strongly against it tonight as well.

1708
02:38:45,229 --> 02:38:51,594
This approach has also jeopardized support for the Zero Waste Project, which is central to our climate action and adaptation plan.

1709
02:38:52,255 --> 02:39:11,891
As the youngest member of this council, I know in my bones that climate change is an existential threat, but something I really worry about are things like this, where the failure of the outreach process means that for too many neighbors, saving the planet now feels synonymous with inconvenience, making people just want to give up on the environment writ large.

1710
02:39:12,749 --> 02:39:17,310
We end up moving farther away from where we need to be, fundamentally undermining the green movement.

1711
02:39:18,330 --> 02:39:24,191
We need to rebuild trust and communicate clearly so residents understand that this doesn't have to be the case.

1712
02:39:25,392 --> 02:39:38,175
I went back to old meeting minutes in my own notes from years ago, and we were told back then that while this could be a future path, the city would for sure conduct comprehensive outreach before moving forward down this path.

1713
02:39:38,695 --> 02:39:39,975
And speaking only for myself,

1714
02:39:41,184 --> 02:39:46,328
I need a clearer plan from the mayor and her administration before I can consider supporting this change.

1715
02:39:47,049 --> 02:39:50,271
